cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.PL, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the security and privacy properties of the BrowserID SSO system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a fix for an authentication bug and discusses the design of a complex web application. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the privacy implications of the BrowserID system. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of new HTML5 features in the BrowserID system. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the BrowserID system employs decentralized login.
